<div id="review_2176961324" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2176961324" />
    <a title="Charlotte May" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14002983-charlotte-may"><img alt="Charlotte May" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1641295530p2/14002983.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2176961324?book_show_action=true">Jun 07, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Charlotte May" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Charlotte May" href="/user/show/14002983-charlotte-may">Charlotte May</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780575079755" href="/book/show/865293.The_Lies_of_Locke_Lamora">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14002983-charlotte-may?shelf=epic-fantasy">epic-fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14002983-charlotte-may?shelf=tear-jerker">tear-jerker</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14002983-charlotte-may?shelf=500-page-plus">500-page-plus</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14002983-charlotte-may?shelf=favourites">favourites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2176961324" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7268159561358274462"><i> “We don’t believe in hard work when a false face and a good line of bullshit can do so much more.” </i><br/><br/>This was great! I don’t really know what I was expecting when I went into <i> The Lies of Locke Lamora </i> But I got an in depth, intricate fantasy world full of morally grey characters and so much backstabbing and double crossing it leaves your head spinning! <br/><br/>Locke Lamora is a member of the Gentlemen’s Bastards, a team of thieves who work up detailed plans in order to swindle the rich nobles out of the</span>
  <span id="freeText7268159561358274462" style="display:none"><i> “We don’t believe in hard work when a false face and a good line of bullshit can do so much more.” </i><br /><br />This was great! I don’t really know what I was expecting when I went into <i> The Lies of Locke Lamora </i> But I got an in depth, intricate fantasy world full of morally grey characters and so much backstabbing and double crossing it leaves your head spinning! <br /><br />Locke Lamora is a member of the Gentlemen’s Bastards, a team of thieves who work up detailed plans in order to swindle the rich nobles out of their money. Locke is so good at these schemes and at evading capture, he’s even been given the nickname the ‘Thorn of Camorr’. <br /><br />We follow Locke as he begins one of his most difficult tricks, all the while numerous other powers are at work. It isn’t long before Locke and his Gentlemen Bastards are caught up in a revenge plot and their lives are on the line. <br /><br />This book doesn’t shy away from both violence and swearing, so be aware if that’s something that would bother you. I enjoyed the similarities it bore to the A Song of Ice and Fire series, but also all the differences that set this book apart. <br /><br />I’m excited to see where the next book takes us! <br /><br /><i> “Justice is red” </i></span>
  <a data-text-id="7268159561358274462" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

